sentence: Friday's session closes with the NASDAQ Composite Index at 5,046.37.
The total shares traded for the NASDAQ was over 2.05 billion.
Advancers stocks led declining by 1.08 to 1 ratio.
There were 1457 advancers and 1354 decliners for the day.
On the NASDAQ Stock Exchange 16 stocks reached a 52 week high and 100 reaching lows.
The most active, advancers, decliners, unusual volume and most active by dollar volume can be monitored intraday on the Most Active Stocks page.
The NASDAQ 100 index closed down -.4% for the day; a total of -18.64 points.
Symantec Corporation ( SYMC ) had the largest percent change down (-7.7%) while Incyte Corporation ( INCY ) had the largest percent change gain rising 5.15%.
The Dow Jones index closed down -.24% for the day; a total of -42.39 points.
Procter & Gamble Company (The) ( PG ) had the largest percent change down (-1.76%) while Caterpillar, Inc. ( CAT ) had the largest percent change gain rising 1.28%.
